  "text": "Activation of the inflammasome is by no means specific to TiO 2 particles although Pele et al. have shown that correct design of in vitro experiments is critical. Notably, cell gorging of particles through extended particle exposure (e.g. over 24 h) can lead to false positives [CITATION_1] . SNPs and MSU crystals are considered exemplar particulate stimulants of the inflammasome, and we confirmed that, with similar short exposures as for our TiO 2 particles (3 h) and LPS priming, IL-1β secretion was enhanced compared to non-particle-exposed cells (Fig. 8) .",
